The paper discusses the issue of unfairness and discrimination in machine learning systems, which falls under the category of "cybersecurity and privacy" (cs.CY) and "cryptography and security" (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and the need for transparency and accountability, which falls under the category of "artificial intelligence" (cs.AI) and "machine learning" (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the legal and governance aspects of algorithmic decision-making, which falls under the category of "computer science and society" (cs.CS).
